<article class="doc">
<h1 class="page">Service synchronization</h1>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>By default, <code>skupper init</code> creates a site that synchronizes all services from other sites that also have synchronization enabled.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>To disable service synchronization:</p>
</div>
<div class="listingblock">
<div class="content">
<pre>$ skupper init --service-sync false</pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>To check whether synchronization is enabled, check the value for <code>service-sync</code> in the output from the following command:</p>
</div>
<div class="listingblock">
<div class="content">
<pre>$ kubectl get cm skupper-site -o json</pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Notes:</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p>When considering whether services are synchronized between two sites, <code>service-sync</code> must be enabled on both sites.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>If you use the command <code>skupper service delete</code> on a site, that command only works if the service was created on that site.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</article>
